<span id="freeTextContainer11528880693867100096">Ê∏ÖÂ∞ëÁ¥çË®Ä in Japanese <br/>Sei Shonagon (c. 966 -1017) was a Japanese author and a court lady who served the Empress Teishi (Sadako) around the year 1000 during the middle Heian period. She is best known as the author of &quot;The Pillow Book&quot; (ÊûïËçâÂ≠ê makura no s≈çshi).<br/></span>
  <span id="freeText11528880693867100096" style="display:none">Ê∏ÖÂ∞ëÁ¥çË®Ä in Japanese <br />Sei Shonagon (c. 966 -1017) was a Japanese author and a court lady who served the Empress Teishi (Sadako) around the year 1000 during the middle Heian period. She is best known as the author of "The Pillow Book" (ÊûïËçâÂ≠ê makura no s≈çshi).<br /></span>
